        <Grid x:Name="Lesson_1_CompoundSentences" Grid.Row="1" Grid.RowSpan="3" Background="AliceBlue" Visibility="Hidden">
            <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto" FontFamily="Josefin Sans">
                <StackPanel Margin="20">
                    <!-- Title -->
                    <TextBlock FontSize="24" FontWeight="Bold" Text="Lesson 2: Compound Sentences in Russian" Margin="0,0,0,20" TextAlignment="Center"/>

                    <!-- Introduction -->
                    <TextBlock FontSize="20" Text="Introduction" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,0,0,10"/>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" TextWrapping="Wrap">
                In this lesson, you will learn about compound sentences in Russian. Compound sentences are used to combine two or more independent clauses into one sentence. Understanding how to form and use compound sentences is essential for expressing complex ideas and constructing more varied sentences in Russian.
                    </TextBlock>

                    <!-- Compound Sentences Explanation -->
                    <TextBlock FontSize="20" Text="Compound Sentences" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="20,20,0,10"/>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" TextWrapping="Wrap">
                A compound sentence in Russian is formed by combining two or more independent clauses using coordinating conjunctions such as "и" (and), "но" (but), "или" (or), "также" (also), and "однако" (however). Each clause in a compound sentence can stand alone as a complete sentence.
                    </TextBlock>

                    <!-- Examples -->
                    <TextBlock FontSize="20" Text="Examples" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="20,20,0,10"/>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" TextWrapping="Wrap">
                Here are some example sentences using compound sentences in Russian:
                    </TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" Margin="10,0,0,0">1. Я читаю книгу, и мой брат играет в футбол. (Ya chitayu knigu, i moy brat igrayet v futbol) - I am reading a book, and my brother is playing football.</TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" Margin="10,0,0,0">2. Мы пошли в парк, но он был закрыт. (My poshli v park, no on byl zakryt) - We went to the park, but it was closed.</TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" Margin="10,0,0,0">3. Ты можешь взять эту книгу, или я возьму её. (Ty mozhesh' vzyat' etu knigu, ili ya voz'mu yeyo) - You can take this book, or I will take it.</TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" Margin="10,0,0,0">4. Она любит читать, также она любит писать. (Ona lyubit chitat', takzhe ona lyubit pisat') - She loves to read, also she loves to write.</TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" Margin="10,0,0,0">5. Я хотел пойти в кино, однако я был слишком занят. (Ya khotel poyti v kino, odnako ya byl slishkom zanyat) - I wanted to go to the movies, however I was too busy.</TextBlock>

                    <!-- Conjunctions Table -->
                    <TextBlock FontSize="20" Text="Coordinating Conjunctions" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="20,20,0,10"/>
                    <Grid Margin="0,0,0,20">
                        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
                            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
                            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
                            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
                            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
                            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
                            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
                        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
                        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
                            <ColumnDefinition Width="120"/>
                            <ColumnDefinition Width="200"/>
                            <ColumnDefinition Width="390"/>
                        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>

                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Conjunction" Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="0" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Russian" Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="1" FontWeight="Bold"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Example" Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="2" FontWeight="Bold"/>

                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="And" Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="0"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="и" Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="1"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Я читаю книгу, и мой брат играет в футбол." Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="2"/>

                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="But" Grid.Row="2" Grid.Column="0"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="но" Grid.Row="2" Grid.Column="1"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Мы пошли в парк, но он был закрыт." Grid.Row="2" Grid.Column="2"/>

                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Or" Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="0"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="или" Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="1"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Ты можешь взять эту книгу, или я возьму её." Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="2"/>

                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Also" Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="0"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="также" Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="1"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Она любит читать, также она любит писать." Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="2"/>

                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="However" Grid.Row="5" Grid.Column="0"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="однако" Grid.Row="5" Grid.Column="1"/>
                        <TextBlock FontSize="18" Text="Я хотел пойти в кино, однако я был слишком занят." Grid.Row="5" Grid.Column="2"/>
                    </Grid>

                    <!-- Conclusion -->
                    <TextBlock FontSize="20" Text="Conclusion" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="20,20,0,10"/>
                    <TextBlock FontSize="18" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,0,0,20">
                In this lesson, you have learned about compound sentences in Russian and how to use coordinating conjunctions to combine independent clauses. Practice creating your own compound sentences to improve your understanding and fluency.
                    </TextBlock>

